-- ================================================================ Phase #3: Memory Management ==================================================================
Phase #3 Abstract: This phase implements the Memory Management Unit (MMU) that allows tasks to ask for memory, write to memory, and free it when they are done.
ULTIMA 2.0 is assumed to have access to only 1024 bytes of RAM. We decided to implement a page size of 128 bytes, leading to a total of 8 blocks in our RAM.
When memory is first allocated, the entire 1024 chars are initialized as dots ("."). If a task of 129 bytes is requested (block_size + 1), the MMU will allocate
2 blocks for the task. When memory is freed, the character will be replaced with a "#". When our ULTIMA.cpp file is ran it will create the tasks, allocate memory
for the tasks, write to memory, and clear the memory when it is done. All of these processes can be seen in the MMU window on the far right.

